<TITLE> Zakir, Sohel remanded in Gautam killing case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 4 (bdnews24.com) -- A Dhaka court on Tuesday ordered 'Kailya' Zakir, arrested by detective police in police sub-inspector Gautam Kumar Roy killing case, into four more days' remand. Metropolitan magistrate Nazrul Islam granted the fresh remand as Detective Branch inspector Ruhul Amin, who is on the case, sought seven more days' custody at the end of a four-day remand for further questioning. The court also sent Rouf Bhuiyan Sohel, another arrested in the case, to three-day remand. Ruhul Amin told bdnews24.com that Zakir was taken on remand on Apr 29. He said another Zakir Hossain, held by RAB, was also remanded for three days. Gautam, working with Bangshal Police Station in the city's older part, was killed on Apr 20 midnight in Dholaikhal area while returning home from duty. Detective Branch and RAB arrested two Zakirs, with both agencies claiming that their man was the main killer of Gautam. 
